      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Indeed, concerns are valid. Empirical studies show mixed results; some indicate a boost to local economies as employees spend their higher earnings, but others point towards job reductions and increased prices as businesses struggle to maintain margins. To apply this thoughtfully, analyze local data if available, and consider phased approaches, such as making cost-saving improvements first, before adjusting prices. Engaging with a local economic development consultant could also provide insights tailored to your town's marketplace. Balancing the well-being of your employees with the sustainability of your business is a challenge many small businesses face in a changing economic landscape.",
